<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="608" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="608" targetBox="[1267,1271,2746,2767]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph blockId="11.[788,1382,1950,2373]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[788,964,2221,2255]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">Distribution.</emphasis>
Chercher Mts on the E side of the Rift Valley in NE Ethiopia.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="608" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[788,1382,1950,2373]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[788,1068,2305,2334]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 114-145 mm, tail 60-65 mm, ear 17-18 mm,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[175,1379,2379,2767]" pageId="11" pageNumber="608">hindfoot 22-24 mm; weight 36-78 g. Dorsum of the Mount Chercher Brush-furred Rat is brown, with light and dark bands. Karyotypeis 2n = 70.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
